The paper deals with a family of structural descriptors for visual data, specifically for image set coding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an improved version of covariance descriptors by extending them to the Log-Euclidean framework, which involves characterizing covariance structure in terms of the arc-cosine kernel and mean centralization on SPD matrices. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions experimental results, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with operations on matrices, which suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
